rget":"recFrC0435yiaHYOu","label":"location"},{"source":"recXiU82RVp1vo67a","target":"rec6yittVQwxJlpye","label":"location"},{"source":"recXiU82RVp1vo67a","target":"recJWNH2OCuUoOz6e","label":"predecessor"},{"source":"recXiU82RVp1vo67a","target":"rec4bAiAcAOo9mPwO","label":"part of"}],"verses":[{"id":"recRsxGlFYkgEuguZ","ref":"Acts.27.13","text":"And when the south wind blew softly, supposing that they had obtained their purpose, loosing thence, they sailed close by Crete.","year":62},{"id":"recUeFXN4paD9tvxU","ref":"Acts.27.14","text":"But not long after there arose against it a tempestuous wind, called Euroclydon.","year":62},{"id":"recGWZJUEdwB3LeaY","ref":"Acts.27.15","text":"And when the ship was caught, and could not bear up into the wind, we let her drive.","year":62},{"id":"recSBS6TArDteGkLW","ref":"Acts.27.16","text":"And running under a certain island which is called Clauda, we had much work to come by the boat:","year":62},{"id":"reclko2EbJ5Yh4Nyw","ref":"Acts.27.17","text":"Which when they had taken up, they used helps, undergirding the ship; and, fearing lest they should fall into the quicksands, strake sail, and so were driven.","year":62},{"id":"recGhaIUtDXdWsQzw","ref":"Acts.27.18","text":"And we being exceedingly tossed with a tempest, the next day they lightened the ship;","year":62},{"id":"recrJA7mB5SyIGUFz","ref":"Acts.27.19","text":"And the third day we cast out with our own hands the tackling of the ship.","year":62},{"id":"rec59oHddrA3kWPAU","ref":"Acts.27.20","text":"And when neither sun nor stars in many days appeared, and no small tempest lay on us, all hope that we should be saved was then taken away.","year":62}]}
